bitfield.description: Current scheme
Function code assigned to TCP3
RTL Version R code
Major revision X code
Custom version code
Minor revision Y code
Used in conjunction with FREE bit to determine the emulation suspend mode.
For GPIO, the FREE bit is fixed at 1, which means GPIO runs free in emulation suspend.
Per bank interrupt enable. 0 = disable, 1 = enable.
Direction of GPIO bank 1 bits, 0 = output, 1 = input.
Direction of GPIO bank 0 bits, 0 = output, 1 = input.
Output drive state of GPIO bank 1 bits, does not affect operation when it is configured as input. Reading it returns the output drive state.
Output drive state of GPIO bank 0 bits, does not affect operation when it is configured as input. Reading it returns the output drive state.
Writing 1 sets the output drive state of GPIO bank 1 bits. Reading it returns the output drive state.
Writing 1 sets the output drive state of GPIO bank 0 bits. Reading it returns the output drive state.
Writing 1 clears the output drive state of GPIO. Reading it returns the output drive state.
Writing 1 clears the output drive state of GPIO. Reading it returns the output drive state.
